Short answer: **No—client-side injection isn’t your only option on SiteGround shared hosting.** You have at least three feasible, low-friction upgrades that don’t require changing hosts.

# Your options (ranked)
1) **PHP SSR (server-side render on SiteGround)** — Best “now”.  
Use a tiny `blog.php` that fetches the WP REST API (including `yoast_head_json`) and **outputs full HTML** (title/description/canonical/OG/Twitter/JSON-LD) on the server. Add one rewrite so `/blog/{slug}/` maps to `blog.php?slug={slug}`. Works on plain shared hosting (Apache + PHP), no Node, no new infra.

2) **SSG (static site generation via GitHub Actions)** — Best long-term.  
A build job pulls posts + Yoast data, emits `/blog/{slug}/index.html` files and a `sitemap.xml`, then deploys via SFTP to SiteGround. Zero runtime dependencies, perfect for crawlers and social scrapers.

3) **Bot-only prerender proxy** — Fast stopgap.  
Use a prerender service (e.g., Prerender.io) via an `.htaccess` snippet to serve prerendered HTML **only** to bots while humans get your current JS page. It works, but it’s an extra moving part and a third-party dependency.

(Keeping what you have now — **pure client-side injection** — is the lowest effort but the weakest for social cards and some crawlers.)

---

## Minimal PHP SSR you can deploy today
Create `/blog.php` in your web root:

```php
<?php
// /blog.php — SSR blog post with Yoast head from WP REST

header('Content-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8');

$WP_API_BASE = 'https://sgmathtuition.com/wp-json';
$FRONTEND_ORIGIN = 'https://sgmathtuition.com';
$ROUTE_BASE = '/blog';

$slug = isset($_GET['slug']) ? trim($_GET['slug']) : '';
if ($slug === '') { http_response_code(404); echo 'Missing slug'; exit; }

function get_json($url) {
  $ch = curl_init($url);
  curl_setopt_array($ch, [
    CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER => true,
    CURLOPT_TIMEOUT => 8,
    CURLOPT_FOLLOWLOCATION => true,
    CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER => ['Accept: application/json']
  ]);
  $res = curl_exec($ch);
  $code = curl_getinfo($ch, CURLINFO_HTTP_CODE);
  curl_close($ch);
  if ($code >= 200 && $code < 300) return json_decode($res, true);
  return null;
}

$fields = implode(',', [
  'id','slug','link','title','excerpt','content','date','modified',
  'yoast_head_json','_links','_embedded'
]);
$q = http_build_query(['slug'=>$slug,'_embed'=>1,'_fields'=>$fields,'per_page'=>1]);

$post = null;
if (!$post) $arr = get_json("$WP_API_BASE/wp/v2/posts?$q");
if (!empty($arr)) $post = $arr[0] ?? null;
if (!$post) { $arr = get_json("$WP_API_BASE/wp/v2/pages?$q"); if (!empty($arr)) $post = $arr[0] ?? null; }
if (!$post) { http_response_code(404); echo 'Not found'; exit; }

function strip_html($html) { return trim(html_entity_decode(strip_tags($html ?? ''))); }
function excerpt($html, $n=160) { $t = preg_replace('/\s+/', ' ', strip_html($html)); return mb_strlen($t)>$n ? mb_substr($t,0,$n-1).'…' : $t; }

$yoast = $post['yoast_head_json'] ?? null;

$canonical = $yoast['canonical'] ?? ($FRONTEND_ORIGIN.$ROUTE_BASE.'/'.$slug.'/');
// Force canonical host to FRONTEND_ORIGIN
$u = parse_url($canonical);
$canonical = $FRONTEND_ORIGIN.(isset($u['path'])?$u['path']:'/').(isset($u['query'])?'?'.$u['query']:'');

$title = $yoast['title'] ?? strip_html($post['title']['rendered'] ?? 'Untitled') . ' | SG Math Tuition';
$desc  = $yoast['description'] ?? excerpt($post['excerpt']['rendered'] ?? $post['content']['rendered'] ?? '', 160);

$ogImg = null;
if (!empty($yoast['og_image'][0]['url'])) {
  $ogImg = $yoast['og_image'][0];
} else {
  $media = $post['_embedded']['wp:featuredmedia'][0] ?? null;
  if ($media) {
    $sizes = $media['media_details']['sizes'] ?? [];
    $pref = $sizes['large'] ?? $sizes['medium_large'] ?? null;
    $ogImg = ['url'=>($pref['source_url'] ?? $media['source_url'] ?? null),
              'width'=>($pref['width'] ?? null), 'height'=>($pref['height'] ?? null),
              'alt'=>($media['alt_text'] ?? '')];
  }
}

$author = '';
if (!empty($post['_embedded']['author'][0]['name'])) $author = $post['_embedded']['author'][0]['name'];

$published = !empty($post['date']) ? date('c', strtotime($post['date'])) : null;
$modified  = !empty($post['modified']) ? date('c', strtotime($post['modified'])) : null;

// Fallback Article schema if Yoast didn't give one
$schema = $yoast['schema'] ?? [
  '@context'=>'https://schema.org',
  '@type'=>'BlogPosting',
  'mainEntityOfPage'=>$canonical,
  'headline'=>strip_html($post['title']['rendered'] ?? ''),
  'description'=>$desc,
  'datePublished'=>$published,
  'dateModified'=>$modified,
  'author'=>$author ? ['@type'=>'Person','name'=>$author] : null,
  'publisher'=>['@type'=>'Organization','name'=>'SG Math Tuition',
    'logo'=>['@type'=>'ImageObject','url'=>'https://sgmathtuition.com/assets/img/logo-512.png']],
  'image'=> $ogImg && !empty($ogImg['url']) ? [$ogImg['url']] : null,
  'url'=>$canonical
];

$contentHTML = $post['content']['rendered'] ?? '';
?>
