**.htaccess rewrite** (place after your canonical host rules):
```apache
# Pretty blog URLs -> PHP SSR
RewriteRule ^blog/([^/]+)/?$ /blog.php?slug=$1 [L,QSA]
```

That’s it: you now serve crawlers and social cards **full HTML on first byte** from SiteGround shared hosting.

